## KEY POINTS
- Framework rename: should be HAIF (Hospital Acupuncture Implementation Framework), not AIHI
- Existing website (acupressure-focused, built by RMIT-funded designer) is outdated, insecure, not mobile-friendly
- DW to build new prototype website with 2-3 style options for ZZ to review
- Same framework applies to both acupressure (nursing, PONV) and acupuncture (ED, registrar-led) — just different titles/examples
- Framework phases: Exploration → Preparation → Implementation → Sustainment (circular diagram preferred)
- Website should be collapsible/interactive — don't show all content at once, especially on mobile
- ZZ purchased hospitalacupuncture.com domain via Crazy Domains
- ZZ needs to send DW the Crazy Domains password so DW can point domain to new site
- ZZ has unpublished paper (10 interviews) that will go on the site once published
- Website should be AI-native: FAQ-driven, structured for AI retrieval
- Existing site costs ~$60/month via WordPress; new approach should reduce this
- ZZ heading to America for conference in ~2 weeks — wants basic site ready before then
- ACTION: DW to create prototype website this afternoon/week
- ACTION: ZZ to forward Crazy Domains credentials and any new content

